SIMPLE: singularly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Singularly
<hw>Sin"gu*lar*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a singular
manner; in a manner, or to a degree, not common to others;
extraordinarily; <as>as, to be <ex>singularly</ex> exact in one's
statements; <ex>singularly</ex> considerate of others.</as></def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Singularly</xex> handsome.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Strangely; oddly; <as>as, to behave
<ex>singularly</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>So as to express one, or the singular
number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Singult</ent>⟦br⟧
